<h4 class="note-head">Effective Date of 1964 Amendment</h4>
<p class="note-body">Section 13 of <plaw congress="88" isprivate="false" number="467">Pub. L. 88–467</plaw> provided that: “The amendments made by this Act shall take effect as follows:</p>
<p class="note-body">“(1) The effective date of section 12(g)(1) of the Securities Exchange Act of 1934, as added by section 3(c) of this Act [section 78<em>l</em>(g)(1) of this title], shall be July 1, 1964.</p>
<p class="note-body">“(2) The effective date of the amendments to sections 12(b) and 15(a) of the Securities Exchange Act of 1934 [sections 78<em>l</em>(b) and 78<em>o</em>(a) of this title], contained in sections 3(a) and 6(a), respectively, of this Act shall be July 1, 1964.</p>
<p class="note-body">“(3) All other amendments contained in this Act [amending this section and sections 77d, 78<em>l</em>, 78m, 78n, 78<em>o</em>, 78<em>o</em>–3, 78p, 78t, 78w, and 78ff of this title] shall take effect on the date of its enactment [Aug. 20, 1964].”</p>
